r/admin model expanded into a richer per-user permission system for the purchase-order workflow, while preserving admin manageability from the existing User Management UI.\n\n## Known facts / evidence\n- The revision prompt exists at `{path_hint}` and describes five roles plus editable permission sets.\n- `nexus/CLAUDE.md` currently documents only two roles: `user` and `admin`.\n- `nexus/src/types/database.ts` defines `UserRole = 'user' | 'admin'`.\n- `nexus/src/app/(protected)/admin/page.tsx` gates the Admin page to `user.role === 'admin'` and renders a User Management view.\n- `nexus/src/components/admin/UserList.tsx` currently supports password changes via a modal; there is no role/permission editor yet.\n- `nexus/src/app/actions/users.ts` only enforces admin access for password changes and user listing.\n\n## Constraints\n- Brownfield Next.js/Supabase app with existing admin gating patterns.\n- No clarified requirement yet on whether permissions must be enforced only in the UI, in server actions, or all the way to database policies.\n- User asked for deep interview, so this mode must clarify rather than implement.\n\n## Unknowns / open questions\n- Is the goal a true authorization model change or mainly a UI/view customization feature?\n- Should roles be mutually exclusive, additive, or decomposed into independent toggles?\n- Must current `admin` users map to `Super Admin`, `Admin`, or both?\n- Which parts of the app beyond the Admin panel and orders UI must enforce the new permissions?\n- What should remain explicitly out of scope for this revision?\n- What decisions may OMX make without further confirmation?\n\n## Decision-boundary unknowns\n- Can OMX design the permission data model and migration strategy on its own?\n- Can OMX rename or replace the existing `role` enum/column?\n- Can OMX infer default role mappings for existing users?\n- Can OMX decide the exact UX pattern for nested role toggles vs per-permission overrides?\n\n## Likely codebase touchpoints\n- `nexus/src/types/database.ts`\n- `nexus/src/app/(protected)/admin/page.tsx`\n- `nexus/src/components/admin/UserList.tsx`\n- `nexus/src/app/actions/users.ts`\n- Supabase schema/migrations under `nexus/supabase/migrations/`\n- Order and artwork UI/components that currently assume only admin vs non-admin behavior\n'''\nsnapshot_path.write_text(content)\nprint(json.dumps({\n    'slug': slug,\n    'timestamp': ts,\n    'snapshot_path': str(snapshot_path.relative_to(root)),\n    'interview_id': str(uuid.uuid4())\n}))\nPY","workdir":"/Users/macbook/Documents/AI Dev Projects/Artwork Review Tool","yield_time_ms":1000,"max_output_tokens":4000} thread_id=019d5247-8044-7113-a227-a181e2c40e45
