sion-boundaries","question":"I found the current system only has `user` and `admin`. For this revision, what should happen to existing accounts by default — should current `admin` users become `Super Admin`, `Admin`, or something else, and should current `user` users start with no special role unless assigned?","answer":"current admin becomes admin. current user should be assigned no special roles. admin should set the new users to their organization.","interpretation":"Default migration should map existing admins to Admin, existing users to no special roles, and admins should assign new users to an organization."},{"round":4,"target":"decision-boundaries","question":"If current admins only become Admin, then what is Super Admin for in this system — specifically, what actions should only a Super Admin be allowed to do that a normal Admin cannot?","answer":"nevermind, no need super admin.","interpretation":"Super Admin is no longer part of Revision 5; the role set should be reduced accordingly."},{"round":5,"target":"decision-boundaries","question":"Your prompt says “if permissions contradict, use the more permissive setting,” which suggests permissions may be additive. Should a user be allowed to have multiple functional roles at once — for example both Vendor and Designer — with the system taking the most permissive result where they overlap?","answer":"yes user can have multiple functional roles at once","interpretation":"Functional roles are additive; users may hold multiple roles simultaneously and overlaps resolve to the most permissive effective permission."},{"round":6,"target":"success","question":"When this revision is “done,” what are the must-have proof points? In other words, what specific behaviors would make you say this roles-and-permissions system is working correctly?","answer":"completed when i can do the following: users can only do and see what their permissions allow. admin can change the permissions for everyone and it updates live, meaning when the admin changes permissions, it will refresh the page that was being viewed by the user who's permissions was updated.","interpretation":"Success requires effective permission-based visibility and actions, plus live propagation of admin permission changes to affected users' active pages."},{"round":7,"target":"constraints","question":"When an admin removes a permission from a user while that user is already on a page editing something, should the system immediately block/save-fail that action on the backend too, or is it enough that the user’s page refreshes and they lose access from that point forward?","answer":"enough that the users page refreshes and they lose access from that point forward","interpretation":"Live permission changes do not need to retroactively cancel in-flight edits; it is sufficient to refresh the affected user's page and enforce the new access from that point forward."}],"current_ambiguity":0.2375,"threshold":0.2,"max_rounds":12,"challenge_modes_used":["contrarian","simplifier","ontologist"],"codebase_context":{"resolved_artifact":".omx/Prompts/Revision 5 Roles & Permissions 3341258577b480648bcaf4b78fafafde.md","current_roles":"user|admin","admin_touchpoints":["nexus/src/app/(protected)/admin/page.tsx","nexus/src/components/admin/UserList.tsx","nexus/src/app/actions/users.ts","nexus/src/types/database.ts"],"explore_fallback":"omx explore unavailable because cargo missing; used local repo inspection instead"},"current_stage":"intent-first","current_focus":"intent","context_snapshot_path":".omx/context/revision-5-roles-permissions-20260403T085555Z.md","readiness_gates":{"non_goals_explicit":true,"decision_boundaries_explicit":true,"pressure_pass_complete":true},"scores":{"intent":0.45,"outcome":0.85,"scope":0.9,"constraints":0.9,"success":0.85,"context":0.8}}} thread_id=019d5247-8044-7113-a227-a181e2c40e45
