2026-04-03T10:28:18.573839Z  INFO session_loop{thread_id=019d5247-8044-7113-a227-a181e2c40e45}:submission_dispatch{otel.name="op.dispatch.user_input" submission.id="019d52e1-d77a-7340-89ba-44953e07ca80" codex.op="user_input"}:turn{otel.name="session_task.turn" thread.id=019d5247-8044-7113-a227-a181e2c40e45 turn.id=019d52e1-d77a-7340-89ba-44953e07ca80 model=gpt-5.4}: codex_core::stream_events_utils: ToolCall: exec_command {"cmd":"python3 - <<'PY'\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\nimport json\n\nroot = Path('/Users/macbook/Documents/AI Dev Projects/Artwork Review Tool')\nomx = root / '.omx'\ninterviews = omx / 'interviews'\nspecs = omx / 'specs'\ninterviews.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\nspecs.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\nslug = 'revision-5-roles-permissions'\nts = datetime.now(timezone.utc).strftime('%Y%m%dT%H%M%SZ')\ninterview_path = interviews / f'{slug}-{ts}.md'\nspec_path = specs / f'deep-interview-{slug}.md'\ncontext_path = '.omx/context/revision-5-roles-permissions-20260403T085555Z.md'\nfinal_ambiguity = 0.125\n\ntranscript = f'''# Deep Interview Transcript Summary: {slug}\n\n- **Created (UTC):** {ts}\n- **Profile:** standard\n- **Context type:** brownfield\n- **Final ambiguity:** 12.5%\n- **Threshold:** 20%\n- **Context snapshot:** `{context_path}`\n\n## Brownfield evidence gathered\n- `.omx/Prompts/Revision 5 Roles & Permissions 3341258577b480648bcaf4b78fafafde.md` is the source prompt artifact.\n- `nexus/src/types/database.ts` currently defines only `UserRole = 'user' | 'admin'`.\n- `nexus/src/app/(protected)/admin/page.tsx` and `nexus/src/app/actions/users.ts` gate admin-only capabilities with `user.role === 'admin'`.\n- `nexus/src/components/admin/UserList.tsx` currently supports password changes but no role/permission editor.\n- `omx explore` was unavailable in this environment because the local Rust/Cargo dependency was missing, so repo inspection was performed directly.\n\n## Condensed Q&A\n1. **Q:** UI-only permission layer or full end-to-end authorization change?  \n   **A:** Full end-to-end authorization.\n2. **Q:** What is explicitly out of scope?  \n   **A:** Custom role builder, audit logs, org-level multi-org permissions, RLS/policy redesign.\n3. **Q:** How should existing accounts map by default?  \n   **A:** Existing admins become Admin. Existing users get no special roles. Admin assigns new users to their organization.\n4. **Q:** What is Super Admin for?  \n   **A:** Not needed; remove Super Admin from scope.\n5. **Q:** Can users have multiple functional roles simultaneously?  \n   **A:** Yes. Permissions are additive and contradictions resolve to the more permissive result.\n6. **Q:** What proves the system is done?  \n   **A:** Users only see/do what permissions allow, and admin permission changes update live by refreshing the affected user's current page.\n7. **Q:** When permissions are revoked during an active session, must in-flight edits be retroactively blocked?  \n   **A:** No. It is enough to refresh the page and enforce new access from that point forward.\n8. **Q:** Why does this matter most?  \n   **A:** Prevent the wrong people from editing things, reduce screen clutter, and improve vendor/designer separation.\n\n## Pressure-pass finding\nThe interview revisited the original “full auth” answer by stress-testing the migration/default-mapping assumption. That follow-up exposed that existing admins should remain Admin, ordinary users should start with no functional roles, and Super Admin should be removed entirely.\n\n## Readiness summary\n- Non-goals: explicit\n- Decision boundaries: explicit\n- Pressure pass: complete\n- Handoff readiness: yes\n'''\n\nspec = f'''# Deep Interview Spec: Revision 5 Roles & Permissions\n\n## Metadata\n- **Slug:** {slug}\n- **Created (UTC):** {ts}\n- **Profile:** standard\n- **Rounds:** 8\n- **Final ambiguity:** 12.5%\n- **Threshold:** 20%\n- **Context type:** brownfield\n- **Context snapshot:** `{context_path}`\n- **Transcript:** `.omx/interviews/{slug}-{ts}.md`\n\n## Clarity Breakdown\n| Dimension | Score |\n|---|---:|\n| Intent | 90% |\n| Outcome | 85% |\n| Scope | 90% |\n| Constraints | 90% |\n| Success | 85% |\n| Context | 80% |\n\n## Intent\nAdd a real permissions system so the wrong people cannot edit the wrong things, the UI hides irrelevant actions, and vendor/designer responsibilities stay clearly separated.\n\n## Desired Outcome\nA brownfield authorization upgrade where Admin can manage user permissions for everyone in their organization, users can hold multiple functional roles simultaneously, the effective permission set determines what each user can see or do, and permission changes propagate live by refreshing affected users' current pages.\n\n## In Scope\n- Replace the current binary `user`/`admin`-only model with a richer permission-capable model for this app.\n- Keep **Admin** as the administrative role; remove **Super Admin** from Revision 5.\n- Support functional roles/permission groups for **Purchaser**, **Designer**, and **Vendor**.\n- Allow a user to hold multiple functional roles at once.\n- Resolve overlapping permissions using the **more permissive** effective result.\n- Let Admin manage permissions for users in the User Management experience.\n- Ensure Admin can assign new users to their organization.\n- Enforce permission-based visibility and editing behavior in relevant app areas, especially the admin/user-management and order/artwork workflows described in the prompt.\n- Live-update affected users after permission changes by refreshing the page they are currently viewing.\n\n## Out of Scope / Non-goals\n- Custom role builder\n- Audit logs\n- Org-level multi-org permissions\n- RLS / policy redesign\n- Super Admin role\n- Retroactively failing an in-flight edit the instant a permission is revoked before the user page refreshes\n\n## Decision Boundaries\nOMX may decide without further confirmation:\n- The internal data model used to represent additive functional roles and effective permissions, as long as it preserves the agreed behavior.\n- The exact UX composition of the User Management modal/section, as long as Admin can edit whole roles and underlying permissions in a clear way.\n- The migration implementation details for mapping existing `admin` users to **Admin** and existing `user` users to no special functional roles.\n- The technical mechanism for “live refresh” (for example realtime event, invalidation signal, or similar), as long as the affected user's page refreshes and access changes take effect from that point forward.\n\nOMX must **not** decide without further confirmation:\n- Reintroducing Super Admin or any extra role hierarchy\n- Expanding scope into audit trails, custom role creation, multi-org authorization, or RLS redesign\n- Changing the agreed permission-conflict rule away from “more permissive wins”\n\n## Constraints\n- Brownfield Next.js + Supabase codebase with current admin checks embedded in UI/server actions.\n- Existing accounts must migrate as follows:\n  - current `admin` -> **Admin**\n  - current `user` -> no special functional roles\n- Admin should assign new users to their organization.\n- Live permission changes only need to take effect after the affected user's current page refreshes; no requirement to kill or fail in-flight edits before that refresh.\n\n## Testable Acceptance Criteria\n1. A user only sees UI elements, columns, actions, and edit capabilities allowed by their effective permissions.\n2. A user cannot successfully use protected capabilities outside their effective permissions after the page is refreshed under the new permission state.\n3. Admin can view users in the organization and change each user's permission set from the User Management experience.\n4. Admin permission changes propagate live to the affected user's active page by forcing/triggering a refresh or equivalent reload behavior.\n5. Existing admins continue to have Admin capabilities after migration.\n6. Existing ordinary users start without any special functional roles after migration.\n7. Users may hold multiple functional roles simultaneously, and overlapping permissions resolve to the more permissive effective behavior.\n8. No Super Admin role appears in the implementation.\n\n## Functional Role Semantics Confirmed So Far\n### Admin\n- Can manage permissions for everyone.\n- Can assign new users to their organization.\n- Existing admins map here by default.\n\n### Purchaser\nPrompt-stated capabilities when enabled:\n- Create new order\n- Change order date\n- Add items\n- Edit item fields: item name, item category, qty, notes, priority, item order status\n- Delete items\n- Archive order\n\n### Designer\nPrompt-stated capability levels:\n- **Disabled:** hide version, artwork status, artwork button\n- **View only:** user can see Version and Artwork Status\n- **Edit:** user can change version, artwork status, and click artwork button\n\n### Vendor\nPrompt-stated capabilities/restrictions:\n- Cannot delete line items unless Purchaser permissions are also enabled\n- Can see priority, item order status, item name, category, qty, artwork version, artwork status, art button, notes\n- Cannot edit qty, item name, item category, artwork version, priority, item order status, artwork status\n- Can click artwork button to open the artwork uploads modal\n\n## Assumptions Exposed + Resolutions\n- **Assumption:** A full authorization change implied a new top-level hierarchy with Super Admin.  \n  **Resolution:** Rejected. Super Admin removed from scope.\n- **Assumption:** Functional roles might be mutually exclusive.  \n  **Resolution:** Rejected. Roles are additive and more-permissive wins on conflicts.\n- **Assumption:** Live permission changes might require immediate backend interruption of active edits.  \n  **Resolution:** Not required. Refresh-then-enforce is sufficient.\n\n## Pressure-pass Findings\nThe highest-risk hidden assumption was migration behavior after choosing “full auth.” Revisiting that answer clarified role defaults, org-assignment expectations, and the removal of Super Admin, which materially changed the likely implementation approach.\n\n## Brownfield Evidence vs Inference\n### Evidence\n- Current app only documents and types `user`/`admin`.\n- Admin page and user actions already have admin-only checks.\n- User Management UI exists but lacks roles/permissions controls.\n\n### Inference\n- Schema changes and broader server enforcement will likely be required to support additive functional roles end-to-end.\n- A realtime or invalidation mechanism will likely be needed to satisfy the live-refresh requirement.\n\n## Technical Context Findings\n- Likely code touchpoints include:\n  - `nexus/src/types/database.ts`\n  - `nexus/src/app/(protected)/admin/page.tsx`\n  - `nexus/src/components/admin/UserList.tsx`\n  - `nexus/src/app/actions/users.ts`\n  - `nexus/supabase/migrations/*`\n  - order/artwork components currently using admin/non-admin logic\n\n## Condensed Transcript\n- Full auth, not UI-only\n- Non-goals fixed: no custom role builder, audit logs, multi-org permissions, or RLS redesign\n- Existing admins remain Admin; users start with no functional roles\n- Super Admin removed\n- Functional roles are additive; more-permissive wins\n- Done means permission-correct visibility/actions plus live refresh after admin changes\n- Live refresh is sufficient; no need to cancel in-flight edits before refresh\n- Business intent: stop wrong edits, reduce clutter, separate vendor/designer responsibilities\n\n## Recommended Handoff\n**Recommended next step:** `$ralplan`\n\nSuggested invocation:\n```text\n$plan --consensus --direct .omx/specs/deep-interview-revision-5-roles-permissions.md\n```\n\nAlternative handoffs:\n- `$autopilot .omx/specs/deep-interview-revision-5-roles-permissions.md`\n- `$ralph .omx/specs/deep-interview-revision-5-roles-permissions.md`\n- `$team .omx/specs/deep-interview-revision-5-roles-permissions.md`\n'''\n\ninterview_path.write_text(transcript)\nspec_path.write_text(spec)\nprint(json.dumps({\n    'interview_path': str(interview_path.relative_to(root)),\n    'spec_path': str(spec_path.relative_to(root)),\n    'final_ambiguity': final_ambiguity\n}, indent=2))\nPY","workdir":"/Users/macbook/Documents/AI Dev Projects/Artwork Review Tool","yield_time_ms":1000,"max_output_tokens":6000} thread_id=019d5247-8044-7113-a227-a181e2c40e45
