2026-04-03T10:58:00.519607Z  INFO session_loop{thread_id=019d52fd-156b-7d73-8985-7da802bc98b0}:submission_dispatch{otel.name="op.dispatch.user_input" submission.id="019d52fd-15c4-7a63-83f6-46bcc3021a05" codex.op="user_input"}:turn{otel.name="session_task.turn" thread.id=019d52fd-156b-7d73-8985-7da802bc98b0 turn.id=019d52fd-15c4-7a63-83f6-46bcc3021a05 model=gpt-5.4}: codex_core::stream_events_utils: ToolCall: exec_command {"cmd":"python3 - <<'PY'\nfrom pathlib import Path\nprd = Path('.omx/drafts/prd-2026-04-03-revision-5-roles-permissions-draft.md')\ntext = prd.read_text()\ntext = text.replace(\n\"12. Self-service registration currently creates a user with display name/email/password only; org assignment happens later, which matches the clarified requirement that Admin assigns new users to an organization (`nexus/src/app/(auth)/register/page.tsx:22-57`).\\n\",\n\"12. Self-service registration currently creates a user with display name/email/password only; org assignment happens later, which matches the clarified requirement that Admin assigns new users to an organization (`nexus/src/app/(auth)/register/page.tsx:22-57`).\\n13. Organization switching code depends on an `org_members` table, but the checked-in migrations list only `001` through `013` and none define `org_members`; Revision 5 should avoid expanding multi-org membership semantics until the actual runtime schema is verified (`nexus/src/app/actions/organizations.ts:7-54`; `nexus/supabase/migrations/001_initial_schema.sql:1-190`).\\n\")\ntext = text.replace(\n\"3. **Live update UX:** permission changes must invalidate affected user sessions/pages quickly without forcing hard logout semantics.\\n\",\n\"3. **Live update UX:** permission changes must invalidate affected user sessions/pages quickly without forcing hard logout semantics.\\n4. **Org-scope fidelity:** Admin must manage only users in the current organization without depending on unverified multi-org membership schema.\\n\")\ntext = text.replace(\n\"Choose **Option A**: retain `users.role` as the admin flag, add a typed permission document + monotonic `permissions_updated_at`/`permissions_version` signal on `users`, and introduce a shared permission resolver used everywhere.\\n\",\n\"Choose **Option A**: retain `users.role` as the admin flag, add a typed permission document + monotonic `permissions_updated_at`/`permissions_version` signal on `users`, and introduce a shared permission resolver used everywhere. Keep Revision 5 org-scoping anchored to the already-used `users.organization_id` field unless runtime verification proves `org_members` is present and reliable.\\n\")\ntext = text.replace(\n\"Implement a centralized permission resolver backed by a structured permission document on `users`, plus org-scoped admin management and realtime refresh on user-row permission updates.\\n\",\n\"Implement a centralized permission resolver backed by a structured permission document on `users`, plus org-scoped admin management and realtime refresh on user-row permission updates. Treat `users.organization_id` as the authoritative org scope for Revision 5 unless a verified schema check proves `org_members` is safe to rely on.\\n\")\ntext = text.replace(\n\"2. Add a structured permission payload on `users` (or a one-to-one sidecar row if migration ergonomics require it) with:\\n\",\n\"2. Add a structured permission payload on `users` (or a one-to-one sidecar row if migration ergonomics require it) with:\\n\")\ntext = text.replace(\n\"3. Define canonical role templates in code, not DB-configurable UI, because custom role builder is out of scope.\\n4. Compute effective permissions via “admin full access” OR additive functional roles OR explicit overrides, with more-permissive wins.\\n\",\n\"3. Define canonical role templates in code, not DB-configurable UI, because custom role builder is out of scope. Validate reads/writes through a shared TypeScript parser/normalizer without adding new dependencies.\\n4. Compute effective permissions via “admin full access” OR additive functional roles OR explicit overrides, with more-permissive wins.\\n5. Use narrow patch writes for permission updates so Admin edits do not overwrite unrelated user profile fields.\\n\")\ntext = text.replace(\n\"2. **Add schema/migration support and migrate existing users**  \\n   Files: new migration after `nexus/supabase/migrations/013_add_purchase_order_archived.sql`, `nexus/src/types/database.ts`.  \\n   Work: extend `users` with permission payload + refresh marker, backfill existing `admin` users to Admin/full access, leave existing `user` users with empty functional roles, and keep registration defaults compatible with later org assignment.\\n\",\n\"2. **Add schema/migration support and migrate existing users**  \\n   Files: new migration after `nexus/supabase/migrations/013_add_purchase_order_archived.sql`, `nexus/src/types/database.ts`.  \\n   Work: extend `users` with permission payload + refresh marker, backfill existing `admin` users to Admin/full access, leave existing `user` users with empty functional roles, and keep registration defaults compatible with later org assignment. During this step, explicitly verify whether `org_members` exists in the runtime database; if not, keep Revision 5 scoping entirely on `users.organization_id`.\\n\")\ntext = text.replace(\n\"- **Risk:** Admin org scoping is bypassed in backend actions.  \\n  **Mitigation:** derive current admin org once per action and filter all user-management queries by it.\\n\",\n\"- **Risk:** Admin org scoping is bypassed in backend actions.  \\n  **Mitigation:** derive current admin org once per action and filter all user-management queries by it.\\n- **Risk:** The checked-in code references `org_members`, but the migration set shown in the repo does not define it.  \\n  **Mitigation:** verify runtime schema before implementation and keep Revision 5 scoped to `users.organization_id` if membership tables are absent or incomplete.\\n\")\ntext = text.replace(\n\"2. Admin sees only users in the same organization and can update their org assignment + permissions from User Management.\\n\",\n\"2. Admin sees only users in the same organization and can update their org assignment + permissions from User Management, using the verified current-org source of truth.\\n\")\ntext = text.replace(\n\"5. Verify migration defaults against seeded/existing admin and user accounts.\\n\",\n\"5. Verify migration defaults against seeded/existing admin and user accounts.\\n6. Verify the runtime org-scoping source (`users.organization_id` and, only if present, `org_members`) matches the chosen implementation path before coding dependent flows.\\n\")\ntext = text.replace(\n\"- Initial deliberate consensus draft created from deep-interview spec + brownfield evidence.\\n\",\n\"- Initial deliberate consensus draft created from deep-interview spec + brownfield evidence.\\n- Architect review improvements applied: clarified org-scope source of truth, added runtime schema verification for `org_members`, and narrowed the permission-document update strategy.\\n\")\nprd.write_text(text)\n\ntest = Path('.omx/drafts/test-spec-2026-04-03-revision-5-roles-permissions-draft.md')\nt = test.read_text()\nt = t.replace(\n\"- `getAllUsers` replacement returns only users in the admin’s organization.\\n\",\n\"- `getAllUsers` replacement returns only users in the admin’s organization, using the verified org-scope source of truth.\\n\")\nt = t.replace(\n\"- Keep target user open on `/orders`; Admin changes permissions; target page refreshes and controls update.\\n\",\n\"- Keep target user open on `/orders`; Admin changes permissions; target page refreshes and controls update.\\n- Confirm the refresh subscription is scoped to the current signed-in user row and does not refresh unrelated sessions.\\n\")\nt = t.replace(\n\"- Existing admin migration + baseline user migration behaviors are confirmed.\\n\",\n\"- Existing admin migration + baseline user migration behaviors are confirmed.\\n- The chosen org-scoping source (`users.organization_id`, and `org_members` only if verified present) is confirmed in runtime/schema inspection.\\n\")\nt = t.replace(\n\"- Because RLS redesign is out of scope, verification must focus on app-layer server actions rather than database-level policy enforcement.\\n\",\n\"- Because RLS redesign is out of scope, verification must focus on app-layer server actions rather than database-level policy enforcement.\\n- If runtime schema differs from the checked-in migrations, implementation must pause long enough to reconcile the org-scoping assumption before shipping.\\n\")\ntest.write_text(t)\nprint('updated drafts')\nPY","workdir":"/Users/macbook/Documents/AI Dev Projects/Artwork Review Tool","yield_time_ms":1000,"max_output_tokens":4000} thread_id=019d52fd-156b-7d73-8985-7da802bc98b0
