r-focused.\\n3. **Live update UX:** permission changes must invalidate affected user sessions/pages quickly without forcing hard logout semantics.\\n4. **Org-scope fidelity:** Admin must manage only users in the current organization without depending on unverified multi-org membership schema.\\n5. **Safe privileged writes:** permission/org updates on `users` must use narrow, server-checked service-role writes because user-table RLS only allows self-update.\\n\")\ntext = text.replace(\n\"3. **Harden user-management backend for org-scoped permission administration**  \\n   Files: `nexus/src/app/actions/users.ts`, `nexus/src/app/(protected)/admin/page.tsx`.  \\n   Work: scope user listing to current admin’s organization, add action(s) to update permissions and assign organization, and replace direct `role === 'admin'` checks with shared permission helpers.\\n\",\n\"3. **Harden user-management backend for org-scoped permission administration**  \\n   Files: `nexus/src/app/actions/users.ts`, `nexus/src/app/(protected)/admin/page.tsx`, `nexus/src/lib/supabase/server.ts`.  \\n   Work: scope user listing to current admin’s organization, add action(s) to update permissions and assign organization, replace direct `role === 'admin'` checks with shared permission helpers, and perform cross-user `users` updates only through `createServiceClient()` after explicit admin/org authorization checks.\\n\")\ntext = text.replace(\n\"- **Risk:** JSON/structured permission payload becomes inconsistent.  \\n  **Mitigation:** central schema validator + migration default factory in `lib/auth/permissions.ts`.\\n\",\n\"- **Risk:** JSON/structured permission payload becomes inconsistent.  \\n  **Mitigation:** central schema validator + migration default factory in `lib/auth/permissions.ts`.\\n- **Risk:** Admin permission updates overreach because the `users` table requires service-role writes for cross-user changes.  \\n  **Mitigation:** funnel all permission/org mutations through a narrow service-role server action that authorizes Admin first, patches only permission/org fields, and never exposes raw service-role calls to the client.\\n\")\ntext = text.replace(\n\"2. Admin sees only users in the same organization and can update their org assignment + permissions from User Management, using the verified current-org source of truth.\\n\",\n\"2. Admin sees only users in the same organization and can update their org assignment + permissions from User Management, using the verified current-org source of truth and a server-side privileged write path.\\n\")\ntext = text.replace(\n\"- Architect review improvements applied: clarified org-scope source of truth, added runtime schema verification for `org_members`, and narrowed the permission-document update strategy.\\n\",\n\"- Architect review improvements applied: clarified org-scope source of truth, added runtime schema verification for `org_members`, and narrowed the permission-document update strategy.\\n- Critic review improvements applied: made the service-role requirement explicit for cross-user `users` mutations and tightened the associated risk/verification language.\\n\")\nprd.write_text(text)\n\ntest = Path('.omx/drafts/test-spec-2026-04-03-revision-5-roles-permissions-draft.md')\nt = test.read_text()\nt = t.replace(\n\"- Non-admin caller cannot update another user’s permissions.\\n- Admin can assign organization to an unassigned user in their org scope.\\n- Permission update writes the refresh marker/version.\\n\",\n\"- Non-admin caller cannot update another user’s permissions.\\n- Admin can assign organization to an unassigned user in their org scope.\\n- Permission/org update path uses the intended server-side privileged write mechanism rather than a plain authenticated `users` update.\\n- Permission update writes the refresh marker/version.\\n\")\nt = t.replace(\n\"- Because RLS redesign is out of scope, verification must focus on app-layer server actions rather than database-level policy enforcement.\\n- If runtime schema differs from the checked-in migrations, implementation must pause long enough to reconcile the org-scoping assumption before shipping.\\n\",\n\"- Because RLS redesign is out of scope, verification must focus on app-layer server actions rather than database-level policy enforcement.\\n- Because cross-user `users` writes require privileged access under current policies, verification must explicitly cover the service-role-backed admin mutation path.\\n- If runtime schema differs from the checked-in migrations, implementation must pause long enough to reconcile the org-scoping assumption before shipping.\\n\")\ntest.write_text(t)\nprint('updated service-role details')\nPY","workdir":"/Users/macbook/Documents/AI Dev Projects/Artwork Review Tool","yield_time_ms":1000,"max_output_tokens":4000} thread_id=019d52fd-156b-7d73-8985-7da802bc98b0
